This paper proposes a technique for making digital resources on the web verifiable, immutable, and permanent, which is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. The use of cryptographic hash values and URIs is related to digital libraries (cs.DL) and security and cryptography (cs.CR). The focus on linked data and RDF graphs suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the emphasis on compatibility with existing standards and protocols and practicality points to software engineering (cs.SE).
